"review_level": "None",
"content": "<h2>Depth as a literal measurement</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen7:20\">GEN 7:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:31\">1KI 7:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs7:35\">1KI 7:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:6\">EZK 40:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:9\">EZK 40:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek40:30\">EZK 40:30</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek43:13\">EZK 43:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts27:28\">ACT 27:28</a></p>\n<h2>Depth indicating the strength of human emotions</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor2:4\">2CO 2:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:60\">LAM 3:60</a></p>\n<h2>Depth as a characteristic of wisdom</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:33\">ROM 11:33</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:9\">PHP 1:9</a></p>\n<h2>Depth representating the immeasurability of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:33\">ROM 11:33</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Depth used to express the love of God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:38-Rom8:39\">ROM 8:38–8:39</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:16-Eph3:19\">EPH 3:16–3:19</a></p>",
